## About

Jesse Lastunen is a research associate at UNU-WIDER, focusing on tax-benefit microsimulation modeling, social policy, taxation and employment. He coordinates SOUTHMOD microsimulation models for Vietnam, Rwanda and Uganda.

## AI for Economists

The AI for Economists page (https://policy.fi/ai-econ/) is a curated collection of resources for economists working with AI and LLMs — research papers, courses, coding guides (Claude Code, Cursor, Stata), AI tools for research (Elicit, Refine.ink), prompt engineering, and commentary from leading economists.

## Key topics

- Tax-benefit microsimulation (SOUTHMOD)
- AI and LLMs for economic research
- Social policy in developing countries
- Generative AI tools for economists
